We also could have noted that $2\sin A = 3\cos A$ gives us $\sin A = \frac32\cos A$, so $\tan A = \frac{\sin A}{\cos A} = \frac{(3/2)\cos A}{\cos A } =\boxed{\frac32}$. The answer is \frac{3}{2}.

